summary: Tenth Doctor: “Hang on, are you wearing plastic shoes... with holes in?”  Donna: “They’re my holiday shoes. Can we go, please?” ...

Donna: “They’re my holiday shoes. Can we go, please?”

Tenth Doctor: “I don’t have companions who wear plastic shoes.”

Donna: Come on, I’ll buy you and ice cream.”

summary: “One belongs to New York instantly, one belongs to it as much in five minutes as in five years.”                               ...
caption:
“One belongs to New York instantly, one belongs to it as much in five minutes as in five years.”

                                                                             — Tom Wolfe

Founded in 1624, New York City has become a point of pride for America as the home to the Statue of Liberty, Empire State Building, Broadway, and more. People come from all over the globe for its people and its attractions. But for most, it’s a place for dreams; for new beginnings; for endless possibilities; for the start of a new life. New York City holds a different and indistinct meaning for everybody. What will it mean to you?

Bright Lights Big City is an appless, OC roleplay set in the five boroughs of New York City. Our doors opened in July of 2016 and have become the home of dozens of members and nearly 100 characters. We’re looking for active, dedicated writers to join our group and find their home with us in the city the never sleeps.

summary: Possible Guest Stars for Big Hero 6 The Series: Series 2
title: Possible Guest Stars for Big Hero 6 The Series: Series 2
body:
Clancy Brown: I bet we get this guy to voice the new main villain in Series 2, once Liv Amara is defeated. Or maybe, he could play some militarian man who works for Liv. 

David Tennant: I can picture this guy voicing a daredevil stuntman villain who causes destruction, alongside the Mad Jacks, should they return. I think the Mad Jacks DEFINITELY need to return.

Leigh-Allyn Baker: I can picture her doing voices for Megan’s mother, or maybe a relative of Karmi, or some villain, or whatever.

Raven-Symoné: Really, I think the star of ‘That’s So Raven’ and ‘Raven’s Home’ could definitely make an appearance in Big Hero 6 the Series Series 2. She would play a new student called Raven, who has a secret ability to show the future, and showing Big Hero 6 when crimes are about to occur. Wasabi would fall in love with her.

Rob Lowe: Definitely, this guy. He could guest star in a episode where Big Hero 6 get visited by a grown-up Hiro Hamada from the future. Rob Lowe would voice grown-up Hiro, who’d also have a bushy goatee.

James Woods: Someone like him could play Langstrom Krei, Alistair Krei’s older brother, who could also possibly work for Liv Amara.

Larry the Cable Guy: A funny redneck guy like him would be perfect for Big Hero 6 The Series. He’d play either a redneck sounding villain, or hero, or monster made by Liv Amara.

Debi Derryberry: She would be perfect for it - after all, she voiced Jimmy Neutron, and Coco Bandicoot, so, what’s stopping her from being in Big Hero 6 the Series?

Tell me what you think of these guest stars!
